      <h2 class="section-heading">
        About the Project
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Orbital Temple is an artwork and a satellite that aims to be a radically inclusive temple, built where no walls can reach. Created by Brazilian artist Edson Pavoni, the artist behind the Inumeráveis Memorial that reached 1 in each 6 Brazilians during the COVID pandemic, the project invites people from around the world to send the name of someone they wish to remember. These names are transmitted to a satellite in orbit, creating a collective memorial.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text body-text--section-end">
        Through a website available in 246 languages, participants engage in a new kind of ritual. The Orbital Temple explores themes of inclusion, memory, and our shared humanity, questioning why no physical temple on Earth can truly welcome everyone, and proposing space as the only place where radical inclusivity might exist.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Facts -->
